    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two spheres of the same diameter labeled Sphere 1 and Sphere 2, suspended from two stands by two strings. Sphere 1 is to the left of Sphere 2, the string supporting Sphere 1 is to the right of the vertical, and the string supporting Sphere 2 is to the left of the vertical. The string supporting Sphere 2 makes a greater angle from the vertical than the string supporting Sphere 1.\" src=\"/images/342a27d311355a0e85e8d742d8eb1366.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two charged spheres, Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, are hanging at rest and are suspended from insulating stands by insulating strings, as shown in the figure. The spheres have the same diameter but different masses. Since the spheres are both charged, the strings do not hang vertically. The string supporting Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> makes a greater angle from the vertical than the string supporting Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. Which of the following claims is correct about the charges on and the masses of the two spheres?</p>\n",
